-- Grana y Montero Plans to Build Eight Housing Projects in Peru
-- B y   A l e x   E m e r y
-- 2012-03-12T16:42:17Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-03-12/grana-y-montero-plans-to-build-eight-housing-projects-in-peru.html
Grana y Montero SA (GRAMONC1) , a Lima-based
construction company, said it will build eight housing projects
in  Peru  “in the medium term” to meet rising demand.  The company aims to build 2,000 homes a year, up from 1,500
in 2011, Chief Executive Officer Jose Grana Miro Quesada said in
a regulatory filing. Peru needs to build 100,000 to 150,000
homes annually to meet demand, he said in the filing.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Alexander Emery in Lima at 
